description.@value: Khamsah of Niẓāmī Decorations:Miniature: Folio 3v: The Prophet on Burāq guided by Jibrā'īl and escorted by angels ascending the heavens. The constellations, signs of the Zodiac and the seven heavens are all depicted. Miniature: Folio 12v: Anūshīrvān and the owls. Miniature: Folio 14v: Sulṭān Sanjar and the old woman. Miniature: Folio 16v: The story of the hunter, the dog and the fox. Miniature: Folio 19v: Jesus and the dead dog. Miniature: Folio 25v: The youth who divulged Jamshīd's secrets to an old woman. Miniature: Folio 29v: Hārūn al-Rashīd and the barber. Folio 34r: The elders pleading on behalf of Khusraw to Hurmuzd. Miniature: Folio 36v: Shāpūr watching a boy taking the portrait of Khusraw down from the tree for Shīrīn to look at. Miniature: Folio 40r: Khusraw and Shīrīn together in bed. Miniature: Folio 42r: Khusraw watching Shīrīn bathing. Miniature: Folio 46v: Khusraw and Shīrīn meeting on the hunting ground. Miniature: Folio 48v: Khusraw killing the lion outside Shīrīn's tent. Miniature: Folio 53r: Battle between Khusraw and Bahrām Chūbīn. Miniature: Folio 57r: Bārbad and Nīgīsa entertaining Khusraw and Shīrīn. Miniature: Folio 64v: Shīrīn visiting Farhād on Mt. Bisitun. Folio 92v: The Prophet on Burāq ascending the heavens preceded by Jibrā'īl who is holding out a flower towards a lion on a cloud. An angel (Isrāfīl?) blowing a seven-headed trumpet. Miniature: Folio 100r: Laylā and Majnūn at school. Miniature: Folio 103v: Majnūn taken to the Ka'bah by his father. Miniature: Folio 107r: Ibn Salām watching Laylā with her companions in the palmgrove. Miniature: Folio 109v: The battle of the tribes. Miniature: Folio 115r: Laylā rejecting Ibn Salām. Miniature: Folio 131v: Laylā and Majnūn fainting. Folio 148r: Bahrām Gūr killing the dragon. Miniature: Folio 155r: Fitnah carrying the ox on her shoulders up steps to Bahrām Gūr. Miniature: Folio 159v: Bahrām Gūr with the Indian Princess in the Black Pavilion. Miniature: Folio 165v: Bahrām Gūr with the Moorish Princess in the Yellow Pavilion. Miniature: Folio 168v: Bahrām Gūr with the Tartar Princess in the Green Pavilion. Miniature: Folio 171v: Bahrām Gūr with the Russian Princess in the Red Pavilion. Miniature: Folio 175v: Bahrām Gūr with the Princess of Khvarazm in the Blue Pavilion. Miniature: Folio 180v: Bahrām Gūr with the Chinese Princess in the Sandalwood Pavilion. Miniature: Folio 184v: Bahrām Gūr with the Greek Princess in the White Pavilion. Miniature: Folio 189v: Bahrām Gūr and the shepherd who hanged his dog. Folio 208r: Iskandar celebrating his victory over the Zangis (Habashis). Miniature: Folio 219v: Iskandar comforting the dying Dārā. Miniature: Folio 232r: Iskandar entertained by Nūshābah. Miniature: Folio 244r: The Khāqān of Chīn brought bound before Iskandar. Miniature: Folio 246r: Iskandar entertained by the Khāqān of Chīn. Miniature: Folio 252r: Iskandar's battle with the Russians. Miniature: Folio 261v: Iskandar and an angel observing Khiz̤r and Ilyās putting the dried fish into the Water of Life. Folio 274r: Hurmus hypnotising the sages who had gathered to defeat him in debate. (Inscription eulogising the patron of the MS., Abu'l-Ḥasan Mīrzā and also stating that the miniature was completed by Ṭālib in 1077 [=1666-1667]).
